 Here's a solution to find the common elements in two arrays without using any extra data structures:
```
function commonElements(arr1, arr2) {
  let result = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < arr1.length; i++) {
    for (let j = 0; j < arr2.length; j++) {
      if (arr1[i] === arr2[j]) {
        result[] = arr1[i];
        break;
      }
    }
  }
  return result;
}
```
This function iterates through both arrays simultaneously, using two nested for loops. Each iteration of the inner loop compares the current element in one array with the current element in the other array. If the elements match, the matching element is added to the result array and the inner loop break's.
 the final return statement returns the result array containing the common elements.

